Other Major Inequalities: 50. Triangle inequality: |a+b| ≤ |a| + |b| 51. Reverse triangle: ||a| - |b|| ≤ |a-b| 52. Minkowski inequality: (Σ|aᵢ+bᵢ|ᵖ)^(1/p) ≤ (Σ|aᵢ|ᵖ)^(1/p) + (Σ|bᵢ|ᵖ)^(1/p) for p≥1 53. Hölder's inequality: Σ|aᵢbᵢ| ≤ (Σ|aᵢ|ᵖ)^(1/p)(Σ|bᵢ|^q)^(1/q) where 1/p + 1/q = 1 54. Power mean inequality: Mₚ ≤ Mᵩ for p ≤ q 55. Chebyshev's inequality: If a₁≥...≥aₙ, b₁≥...≥bₙ: Σaᵢbᵢ ≥ (Σaᵢ)(Σbᵢ)/n 56. Rearrangement inequality: Sorted pairs give max, reverse-sorted give min 57. Schur's inequality: xʳ(x-y)(x-z) + yʳ(y-z)(y-x) + zʳ(z-x)(z-y) ≥ 0 for r>0 58. Muirhead's inequality (majorization): [a,b,c] ≻ [d,e,f] implies Σxᵃyᵇzᶜ ≥ Σxᵈyᵉzᶠ 59. Jensen's inequality: For convex f: f((x₁+...+xₙ)/n) ≤ (f(x₁)+...+f(xₙ))/n 60. Karamata's inequality: Generalization of Jensen for majorization 61. Nesbitt's inequality: a/(b+c) + b/(c+a) + c/(a+b) ≥ 3/2 62. QM-AM-GM-HM: Quadratic mean ≥ AM ≥ GM ≥ HM

Inequality Techniques: 63. Homogenization: Make all terms same degree 64. Normalization: Set sum or product = 1 65. Substitution: a+b+c=3, abc=1, etc. 66. SOS (Sum of Squares): Express as Σ(...)² ≥ 0 67. Smoothing: Replace (a,b) with ((a+b)/2, (a+b)/2) to improve 68. Mixing variables: Perturbation arguments 69. Buffalo Way: Expand and compare terms systematically

