Fundamental Properties: 126. Division algorithm: a = bq + r, 0 ≤ r < b, unique q,r 127. Divisibility notation: a|b means b = ka for some integer k 128. Transitive: If a|b and b|c, then a|c 129. Linear combination: If a|b and a|c, then a|(mb+nc) for any integers m,n 130. gcd properties: gcd(a,b) = gcd(a, b mod a) = gcd(b, a mod b) 131. Bézout's identity: gcd(a,b) = ax + by for some integers x,y 132. Euclidean algorithm: Recursive gcd computation 133. Extended Euclidean: Finds x,y in Bézout 134. lcm relationship: lcm(a,b)·gcd(a,b) = ab 135. Relatively prime: gcd(a,b) = 1

