Basic Definitions: 289. Graph G = (V,E): Vertices and edges 290. Degree deg(v): Number of edges incident to v 291. Path: Sequence of distinct vertices with edges between consecutive 292. Cycle: Path returning to start 293. Connected: Path exists between any two vertices 294. Tree: Connected acyclic graph 295. Forest: Disjoint union of trees 296. Complete graph Kₙ: All possible edges, |E| = n(n-1)/2 297. Bipartite graph: V = A∪B, all edges between A and B 298. Complete bipartite Kₘ,ₙ

