B. Coordinate Geometry
Line Equations: 408. Slope-intercept: y = mx + b 409. Point-slope: y - y₁ = m(x - x₁) 410. Two-point form: (y-y₁)/(y₂-y₁) = (x-x₁)/(x₂-x₁) 411. Intercept form: x/a + y/b = 1 412. General form: ax + by + c = 0 413. Normal form: x cos α + y sin α = p 414. Parametric: x = x₁ + at, y = y₁ + bt 415. Slope: m = (y₂-y₁)/(x₂-x₁) = -a/b (from ax+by+c=0) 416. Perpendicular lines: m₁m₂ = -1 417. Parallel lines: m₁ = m₂ 418. Distance from point to line: d = |ax₀+by₀+c|/√(a²+b²) 419. Angle between lines: tan θ = |(m₁-m₂)/(1+m₁m₂)|

Section Formula: 420. Internal division: P = ((mx₂+nx₁)/(m+n), (my₂+ny₁)/(m+n)) for ratio m:n 421. External division: P = ((mx₂-nx₁)/(m-n), (my₂-ny₁)/(m-n)) 422. Midpoint: ((x₁+x₂)/2, (y₁+y₂)/2) 423. Centroid: ((x₁+x₂+x₃)/3, (y₁+y₂+y₃)/3)

