Conic Sections:

Parabola: 433. Standard: y² = 4ax (vertex origin, focus (a,0), directrix x=-a) 434. General vertex form: (y-k)² = 4a(x-h) 435. Vertical: x² = 4ay 436. Focal chord: Endpoints (at₁², 2at₁) and (at₂², 2at₂) with t₁t₂ = -1 437. Tangent at (x₁,y₁): yy₁ = 2a(x+x₁) 438. Parametric: (at², 2at) 439. Latus rectum = 4a 440. Reflection property: Ray parallel to axis reflects through focus

