E. Sum-to-Product (for factoring)
sin A + sin B = 2sin((A+B)/2)cos((A-B)/2)
sin A - sin B = 2cos((A+B)/2)sin((A-B)/2)
cos A + cos B = 2cos((A+B)/2)cos((A-B)/2)
cos A - cos B = -2sin((A+B)/2)sin((A-B)/2)
V. COMBINATORICS — Essential Formulations
A. Counting Basics
Permutations: P(n,r) = n!/(n-r)!
Combinations: C(n,r) = n!/[r!(n-r)!]
Permutations with repetition: n!/(n₁!n₂!...nₖ!) where nᵢ are counts of identical objects
Circular permutations: (n-1)!
B. Binomial Coefficients
C(n,r) = C(n,n-r)
Pascal's Identity: C(n,r) = C(n-1,r-1) + C(n-1,r)
Vandermonde: C(m+n,r) = Σ C(m,k)C(n,r-k)
Sum of row: Σ C(n,r) = 2ⁿ
Alternating sum: Σ (-1)ʳC(n,r) = 0
C. Stars and Bars
Non-negative integer solutions to x₁+...+xₖ = n: C(n+k-1, k-1)
Positive integer solutions to x₁+...+xₖ = n: C(n-1, k-1)
D. Inclusion-Exclusion
Two sets: |A∪B| = |A| + |B| - |A∩B|
Three sets: |A∪B∪C| = |A| + |B| + |C|
|A∩B| - |B∩C| - |C∩A| + |A∩B∩C|
Derangements: !n = n!(1 - 1/1! + 1/2! - ... + (-1)ⁿ/n!)
E. Pigeonhole Principle
Basic: n+1 objects in n boxes → some box has ≥2 objects
Generalized: kn+1 objects in n boxes → some box has ≥k+1 objects
Average form: If average is μ, then max ≥ μ and min ≤ μ
VI. SEQUENCES & SERIES — Essential Formulations
A. Arithmetic Progression
General term: aₙ = a₁ + (n-1)d
Sum: Sₙ = n(2a₁ + (n-1)d)/2 = n(a₁+aₙ)/2
Sum of first n integers: 1+2+...+n = n(n+1)/2
B. Geometric Progression
General term: aₙ = a₁rⁿ⁻¹
Sum (finite): Sₙ = a₁(1-rⁿ)/(1-r) for r≠1
Sum (infinite, |r|<1): S = a₁/(1-r)
C. Special Sums
Sum of squares: 1² + 2² + ... + n² = n(n+1)(2n+1)/6
Sum of cubes: 1³ + 2³ + ... + n³ = [n(n+1)/2]²
Telescoping: Σ(aₙ - aₙ₊₁) = a₁ - aₙ₊₁
VII. CALCULUS — Essential Formulations (for JEE)
A. Differentiation
Power rule: d/dx(xⁿ) = nxⁿ⁻¹
Product rule: d/dx(fg) = f'g + fg'
Quotient rule: d/dx(f/g) = (f'g - fg')/g²
Chain rule: d/dx[f(g(x))] = f'(g(x))·g'(x)
Standard derivatives: 141. d/dx(sin x) = cos x 142. d/dx(cos x) = -sin x 143. d/dx(tan x) = sec²x 144. d/dx(eˣ) = eˣ 145. d/dx(ln x) = 1/x

B. Integration
∫ xⁿ dx = xⁿ⁺¹/(n+1) + C (n≠-1)
∫ 1/x dx = ln|x| + C
∫ eˣ dx = eˣ + C
∫ sin x dx = -cos x + C
∫ cos x dx = sin x + C
Integration by parts: 151. ∫ u dv = uv - ∫ v du

Fundamental Theorem: 152. ∫ₐᵇ f(x)dx = F(b) - F(a) where F' = f

C. Limits
lim(x→0) (sin x)/x = 1
lim(x→0) (eˣ-1)/x = 1
lim(x→∞) (1+1/x)ˣ = e
L'Hôpital: If lim f/g is 0/0 or ∞/∞, then lim f/g = lim f'/g'
VIII. GRAPH THEORY (Essential for Combinatorics)
Handshaking Lemma: Σ deg(v) = 2|E|
Tree with n vertices has exactly n-1 edges
Euler Circuit exists ⟺ all vertices have even degree (connected graph)
Euler Path exists ⟺ exactly 0 or 2 vertices have odd degree
