Strategy 2: Use \includeonly for Selective Compilation
Keep single Overleaf project, but compile selectively.

In main.tex:

latex
\documentclass[12pt,twoside,openright]{book}

% ... [all your preamble/packages] ...

% ============================================
% SELECTIVE COMPILATION
% Comment/uncomment to control what compiles
% ============================================

% Option A: Compile everything (WARNING: May timeout on Free tier after ~400 pages)
% [Leave includeonly commented out to compile all]

% Option B: Compile only specific chapters (FAST, use during daily writing)
\includeonly{
    chapters/02-pillar1-framework,
    commentaries/algebra/commentary-023-vieta-roots
}

% Option C: Compile full Part I only
% \includeonly{
%     chapters/01-introduction,
%     chapters/02-pillar1-framework,
%     chapters/03-pillar2-archetypes,
%     chapters/04-pillar3-multidirectional,
%     chapters/05-pillar4-cep-design,
%     chapters/06-pillar5-gems,
%     chapters/07-theorems,
%     chapters/08-certification,
%     chapters/09-transfer,
%     chapters/10-conclusion
% }

% Option D: Compile only today's commentaries batch
% \includeonly{
%     commentaries/algebra/commentary-020-discriminant,
%     commentaries/algebra/commentary-021-vieta-symmetric,
%     commentaries/algebra/commentary-022-binomial-expansion
% }

% ============================================

\begin{document}

\frontmatter
\tableofcontents  % Still generates full TOC even with includeonly

\mainmatter

% Use \include (not \input) for selective compilation to work
\include{chapters/01-introduction}
\include{chapters/02-pillar1-framework}
% ... [all chapters] ...

\include{commentaries/algebra/commentary-001-quadratic-roots}
\include{commentaries/algebra/commentary-002-polynomial-factor}
% ... [all 500 commentaries] ...

\appendix
\include{appendices/appendix-a-gem-catalog}
% ... [all appendices] ...

\end{document}
How it works:

\includeonly{file1,file2} tells LaTeX: "Only compile these files, skip the rest"
BUT: Table of contents, cross-references, page numbers stay correct (uses auxiliary files)
Result: Compile only 2-3 files you're working on today → 5-10 seconds ✅
