STEP 1: Review What You've Completed (5 min)
In Overleaf:

Open each project you worked on in the last 2 weeks
Note which files were created/modified
Quick checklist:
✅ All sections compile without errors?
✅ All examples tested and correct?
✅ All TODOs resolved (or noted for later)?
✅ Formatting looks good?
STEP 2: Download Completed Files (10 min)
For each Overleaf project:

Option A: Download individual files

Click each completed .tex file → three-dot menu → Download
Save to ~/Downloads/overleaf-backup-[date]/
Option B: Download entire project (faster if many files changed)

Menu → Download → Source
Extracts .zip to ~/Downloads/overleaf-backup-[date]/
Pro tip: Create dated backup folder

bash
mkdir -p ~/Downloads/overleaf-backup-$(date +%Y%m%d)
# Example: ~/Downloads/overleaf-backup-20250102
STEP 3: Organize in Local Git Repo (10 min)
bash
cd ~/Documents/advaitian-philosophy

# Copy files from download folder to proper locations
# Example for Pillar 2 work:

cp ~/Downloads/overleaf-backup-20250102/pillar2-archetypes/chapter-archetypes-transformation.tex \
   pillar2-archetypes/

# Example for commentaries:
cp ~/Downloads/overleaf-backup-20250102/algebra-commentaries/commentary-045-amgm.tex \
   commentaries/algebra/commentary-045-amgm-optimization.tex

cp ~/Downloads/overleaf-backup-20250102/algebra-commentaries/commentary-046-cauchy.tex \
   commentaries/algebra/commentary-046-cauchy-schwarz-inequality.tex

# Continue for all modified files...
